The paper addresses the problem of classifying documents in digital libraries, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of machine learning algorithms for classification suggests a focus on topics such as machine learning (cs.LG) and deep learning (cs.DL). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of metadata, which could be related to cybersecurity (cs.CY) in terms of ensuring the accuracy and completeness of data.
